name: Moonshine in Maroc (Signed)
description:
'Moonshine in Maroc' is a visual story book about the time I spent in Morocco, mainly the small surf town of Taghazout during 2011. The word "moonshine" is a metaphor the for the vivid, twilight white glow thats seen throughout the book, and also a metaphor to describe the quirky and mysterious far away land of Morocco - Aaron Keogh.

For a limited time the price of the book is £10 with free worldwide shipping.

FAQ: Their is nowhere to input my shipping address? 
The address you used to sign-up to PayPal will be the primary shipping address that gets send to me. If you have paid for a book but aren't sure your address was correct you can e-mail me at: aarondkeogh@googlemail.com
